    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What school catchments cover Cannon Hill Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cannon Hill State School is the local state primary for most of the suburb. Seven Hills State School also serves parts of the area depending on the specific address. Cannon Hill Anglican College is a nearby private school option from prep through to year 12, which draws families specifically to the inner east corridor. Buyers targeting school catchments should verify their specific address against current Brisbane City Council catchment maps before committing."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Cannon Hill affected by flood risk?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Parts of Cannon Hill near Bulimba Creek carry flood overlay designations. Properties on lower-lying streets in the creek corridor warrant a flood search as standard due diligence. Buyers should obtain a flood certificate from Brisbane City Council for any property under consideration, and should specifically ask a building and pest inspector to assess drainage and any historical water ingress. Not all of Cannon Hill is affected, but it is not a suburb to assume the all-clear without checking the specific address."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What types of properties are most common in Cannon Hill?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cannon Hill's housing stock is a mix of post-war homes, character Queenslanders in varying states of renovation, and a growing number of townhouses and units concentrated around the Cannon Hill train station precinct. Post-war brick and weatherboard homes on 400 to 600 square metre blocks make up much of the detached housing supply. Newer attached dwellings have been added gradually through infill development and represent a separate, more affordable entry point into the suburb."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How competitive is the Cannon Hill property market for buyers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cannon Hill sees a broader and more diverse buyer pool than the prestige inner east suburbs. Listing volumes are reasonable relative to its neighbours, which means buyers have more opportunities to move at a considered pace. That said, well-priced properties in good condition attract multiple buyers quickly. Finance pre-approval, a clear brief, and registration with agents working the suburb remain the practical minimum for any buyer serious about purchasing here."
      }
